(42, 14, 18, 42, 17, 26, 31, 'I must needs go and see it', 'Excuses and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of people making excuses and being preoccupied with daily life, ultimately leading to their destruction. In Luke 14:18, the excuse of attending to land parallels the indifference seen in Luke 17:26-31, where people are engaged in normal activities until judgment comes.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
