(42, 14, 21, 40, 11, 5, 5, 'the poor, and the maimed, and the halt, and the blind', 'Connection of Healing and Inclusion', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusion of the marginalized, such as the blind and the poor. Luke highlights the master sending his servant to bring in the poor and the blind, while Matthew lists the blind receiving sight and the poor hearing the gospel.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
