(42, 14, 21, 40, 22, 7, 8, 'the poor, and the maimed, and the halt, and the blind', 'Invitation to the Marginalized', 'Both passages emphasize the response to rejection by inviting those who are marginalized. In Luke, the master sends his servant to bring in the poor and blind, while in Matthew, the king invites others after the initial guests are deemed unworthy.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 21, 42, 14, 24, 24, 'bring in hither the poor', 'Invitation and Exclusion Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of invitation and exclusion. In Luke 14:21, the master commands to bring in the marginalized, while in Luke 14:24, he declares that those initially invited will not partake.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 21, 43, 9, 39, 39, 'the poor, and the maimed, and the halt, and the blind', 'Blindness and Sight Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of bringing in those who are marginalized, as seen in Luke''s call to the poor and blind, and Jesus'' statement about those who do not see gaining sight. Both passages emphasize the reversal of expectations regarding who is included in God''s kingdom.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
