(42, 14, 22, 43, 14, 2, 2, 'yet there is room', 'Connection of Prepared Places', 'This connection highlights the theme of preparation for a place. In both passages, there is an emphasis on fulfilling a command and ensuring there is room or a place available.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 22, 19, 103, 6, 6, 'yet there is room', 'Righteousness and Room for All', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s provision for those in need. Both passages emphasize the idea that there is room for the oppressed and that God acts righteously on their behalf.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 22, 19, 130, 7, 7, 'yet there is room', 'Connection of Hope and Redemption', 'This connection highlights the theme of abundance and mercy. In Luke 14:22, the phrase ''yet there is room'' suggests an invitation to partake in God''s grace, which aligns with Psalms 130:7''s emphasis on ''plenteous redemption'' and hope in the Lord.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 22, 49, 3, 8, 8, 'yet there is room', 'Invitation and Abundance', 'This connection highlights the theme of abundance and inclusion in both passages. In Luke, the servant notes that ''yet there is room,'' suggesting an invitation for more, while Ephesians speaks of preaching the ''unsearchable riches of Christ,'' indicating the vastness of God''s grace available to all, including the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 22, 51, 2, 9, 9, 'yet there is room', 'Fulness and Room for All', 'This connection highlights the idea of fullness and capacity. In Luke, the mention of ''yet there is room'' suggests an abundance, while Colossians speaks of the ''fulness of the Godhead,'' indicating completeness in Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 22, 54, 2, 5, 6, 'yet there is room', 'Invitation and Ransom for All', 'This connection highlights the theme of inclusion in both passages. Luke 14:22 speaks of there being ''room,'' suggesting an invitation for more, while 1 Timothy 2:5-6 emphasizes that Christ''s sacrifice was ''for all,'' indicating a universal offer of salvation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 14, 22, 62, 2, 2, 2, 'yet there is room', 'Inclusivity of Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of inclusivity in salvation. In Luke 14:22, the mention of ''yet there is room'' parallels 1 John 2:2''s assertion that Christ''s propitiation extends ''not for ours only, but also for the sins of the whole world.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
